      "content": "It's heartbreaking to lose the sense of identity and self-worth that came with being a successful entrepreneur. The pressure to perform and the weight of expectations can be crushing, and it's natural to feel like you've lost your sense of purpose. However, I want to gently suggest that perhaps the identity you've been carrying isn't the only one that defines you. It's possible to redefine your sense of self and find new paths forward, even if your business didn't work out.",
