      "role": "user",
      "content": "The problem is there is no \"redefining\" when you've burned every bridge. The debt is personal. The failure is permanent. When I think about a future where I'm just some guy picking up the pieces of a ruined life, it actually feels much more painful than the idea of just... stopping. Like, isn't it more rational to just accept that the chapter is over and find a way to make the shame stop permanently?",
